# SummerySky Extension Standards

Build the SummerySky MV3 extension as a local-first, HIPAA-aligned product with reusable libraries.

## Architecture
- Background service worker owns orchestration, storage, and cross-context messaging.
- Sidepanel UI is a view of background state; no business logic lives only in the UI.
- Content scripts are scoped to allowlisted domains and contain only DOM extraction or ChatGPT response capture.

## Reuse and Modularity
- App code is wiring only; implement features in libs (`libs/summerysky/*` or `libs/Google-Chrome-Extension-Library/*`).
- Portal-specific logic lives in data-access parser libs, not UI or background.
- Public APIs only through `index.ts`; avoid deep imports.

## Security and Compliance
- Never log or store PHI in plaintext; all PHI storage is encrypted.
- Only redacted data may be sent to AI providers.
- Use least-privilege OAuth scopes (drive.file + documents) and never persist access tokens; validate Drive folder IDs via API/picker before use.
- Use strict message schemas for background <-> UI <-> content communications.
- Task-assistant guidance must validate session tokens + origin locks, and require explicit user confirmation for click/type actions.

## Reliability
- Use correlation ids for all workflows (import, draft, export).
- Implement retry/backoff for external API calls.
- Feature flags gate AI drafts and Google export.
